The paper discusses software design issues related to the development of parallel computational intelligence algorithms on multi-core CPUs, using the new Java 8 functional programming features. It focuses on probabilistic graphical models (PGMs) and presents the parallelization of a collection of algorithms that deal with inference and learning of PGMs from data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SE (Software Engineering), and cs.PL (Programming Languages).
